        "Question": "If Bernard's disposition of the property was void, what governs the partition upon termination of cohabitation? ",
        "Answer": "If the property was acquired by Dorothy and Bernard during their cohabitation, which ended when they physically separated, the property, if found to be co-owned, must be partitioned equally between them. The law states that upon termination of the cohabitation, the corresponding share of the party who did not act in bad faith will comprise his or her share in the co-ownership. Bernard, having disposed of the common property without consent, acted in bad faith, hence Dorothy is entitled to her share in the co-ownership as well as the portion pertaining to Bernard."
