        "Question": "Briefly explain whether the following contract is valid, rescissible, unenforceable, or void: A contract of sale between Lana and Andy wherein 16-year old Lana agreed to sell her grand piano for 25,000.00. ",
        "Answer": "The contract of sale is **voidable**. A contract where one of the parties is incapable of giving consent is voidable under the Civil Code. Lana, being only 16 years old, is incapable of giving consent, which renders her contract with Andy voidable under Article 1390 of the Civil Code."
