        "Question": "(a) Jovencio operates a school bus service for a limited clientele, transporting students for a fee. Did his operation of the school bus service render Jovencio a common carrier? Explain your answer. ",
        "Answer": "Yes, Jovencio may be considered a **common carrier**. Article 1732 of the Civil Code avoided any distinction between a person offering transportation on a regular or an isolated basis, or whether the service is offered to the general public or only to a narrow segment. Jovencio was (a) engaged in transporting passengers generally as a business, (b) undertaking to carry passengers over established roads by the method conducted, and (c) transporting students for a fee. Despite catering to a limited clientele, he held himself out as a ready transportation indiscriminately to the students of a particular school."
