        "subject": "Civil Law",
        "No": 421,
        "Question": "Should Mr. Reyes be granted custody of C? Explain. ",
        "Answer": "No, Mr. Reyes should not be granted custody of C. C is an illegitimate child. An illegitimate child shall be under the **sole parental authority of the mother** unless the mother is unfit to have custody of her child (Tonog vs. Court of Appeals, G.R. No. 122906, February 7, 2002). There appears to be no allegation or showing that Ms. Cruz is unfit. Mr. Reyes' recognition of the child may be a good ground to order him to support C, but not to grant him custody (Briones v. Miguel, G.R. No. 156343 October 18, 2004)."
