        "subject": "Civil Law",
        "No": 426,
        "Question": "Name at least two (2) exclusions from the following property regimes as enumerated under the Family Code: (b) Conjugal partnership of gains ",
        "Answer": "Under Article 109 of the Family Code, the following are excluded from the conjugal partnership of gains: 1) **Property brought to the marriage as exclusive property by either spouse**; 2) **Property acquired by gratuitous title by either spouse during the marriage**; 3) Property acquired by right of redemption, barter or exchange with property belonging to only one of the spouses; 4) Property purchased with exclusive money of the wife or husband."
