        "No": 432,
        "Question": "Within what period should A, B, and C file the complaint for quieting of title? Explain. ",
        "Answer": "A, B, and C may file the complaint for quieting of title **at any time because the cause of action to quiet title is imprescriptible**. An action to quiet title may be filed anytime especially if the property is still in the possession of the true owner (Article 476-477, Civil Code)."
