        "Answer": "Yes, A may file the complaint for quieting of title on behalf of the heirs even without the knowledge and consent of B and C. In a **co-ownership**, any one of the co-owners may file an action in court to preserve or protect the interest of all the co-owners, even without the express authority of his co-owners. Quieting of title is considered an **act of preservation** (Article 487, Civil Code)."
