        "Question": "S Company, a surety for debtor D, claimed that its liability was extinguished because creditor C granted D an extension of the period of payment without S Company's knowledge. Will the defense of S Company prosper? Explain. ",
        "Answer": "Yes, the defense of S Company **will prosper**. In a contract of guaranty or suretyship, any material alteration of the principal obligation without the consent of the guarantor or surety extinguishes the obligation of the surety or guarantor. The extension of the period of payment of the principal debtor amounts to a **novation of the obligation** which releases the surety (Security Bank and Trust Co. vs. Cuenca G.R. No. 138544 October 3, 2000)."
