        "Question": "Assuming that O could no longer recover the subject property in view of X's registration thereof in his name, may a claim against the Assurance Fund pursuant to the provisions of the Property Registration Decree be instituted? Explain. ",
        "Answer": "Yes, a claim against the Assurance Fund **may be instituted**. The law states that a person who sustains loss or damage, or is deprived of any interest in land... through fraud or in consequence of any error... and who by the provisions of the decree is barred or otherwise precluded from bringing an action for the recovery of such land or interest therein, may bring an action for the recovery of damages to be paid out of the **Assurance Fund**. Since the property is already registered in the name of an innocent purchaser for value (X) and O may no longer recover the land, an action for recovery against the Assurance Fund is warranted."
