        "Answer": "The contention of Mr. A (creditor) that the partners are solidarily liable is **not correct**. Under Article 1816, all partners shall be liable **pro rata** with all their property only after all the partnership assets have been exhausted. The liability is not solidary unless the obligation falls under Articles 1822 and 1823. The contention of X, Y, and Z (lessees) that they may suspend the payment of rentals is correct. They may suspend the payment of rentals if they opt to continue with the lease, provided that the lessor fails to make the necessary repairs on the property leased (Article 1658, Civil Code)."
