        "Question": "A minor student, while under the supervision of the school, caused injury to another person. What is the nature of the liability of the parents and the school? Explain briefly.",
        "Answer": "In case of injury caused by a minor (child), the parents are generally liable for the damages caused. However, since the incident happened inside the school, the child was under the **special parental authority** of the school (Family Code, Art. 218). Consequently, the liability of the school is **primary**, while that of the parents is **subsidiary** (Family Code, Art. 219)."
