        "Question": "A Japanese national was able to obtain a divorce decree concerning his marriage with his Filipino wife. The decree capacitated the Japanese national to remarry. Does the Filipino wife need to obtain a judicial recognition of the divorce decree before she can remarry? Explain briefly.",
        "Answer": "Yes, the Filipino spouse must obtain a **judicial recognition** of the divorce decree before she can remarry. Our courts do not take judicial notice of foreign judgments and laws (Sakai v. Republic). This means that the foreign judgment and its authenticity must be proven as facts under our rules on evidence, together with the alien's applicable national law."
