        "subject": "Civil Law",
        "No": 532,
        "Question": "Lloyd had a long-time crush with his childhood friend Miggy. Lloyd migrated to Sweden, became a naturalized Swedish citizen, underwent gender-affirming surgery, and changed his name to Laida. Laida returned to the Philippines and married Miggy. Is the marriage between Miggy and Laida valid? Explain.",
        "Answer": "Yes, the marriage between Miggy and Laida is considered valid. Under Article 15 of the Civil Code, laws relating to family rights, duties, and to the status, condition and legal capacity of persons are binding upon citizens of the Philippines even though living abroad. However, this nationality principle applies only to Filipino citizens and cannot be imposed on foreigners. Laida has been naturalized as a Swedish citizen prior to the gender-affirming surgery and change of name which were done in accordance with Swedish law. Therefore, Laida’s capacity to marry shall be governed by her national law."
