        "Question": "Write 'TRUE' if the statement is true or 'FALSE' if the statement is false. If the statement is FALSE, state the reason. Roberta, a Filipino, 17 years of age, without the knowledge of his parents, can acquire a house in Australia because Australian Laws allow aliens to acquire property from the age of 16.",
        "Answer": "TRUE. Since Australian Law allows aliens to acquire property from the age of 16, Roberta may validly own a house in Australia, following the principle of lex rei sitae enshrined in Art. 16, NCC which states: 'Real property as well as personal property is subject to the law of the country where it is situated.' Moreover, even assuming that legal capacity of Roberta in entering the contract in Australia is governed by Philippine law under Art. 15, NCC, the contract of sale is not void but merely voidable under the NCC. Hence, even under Philippine law, she will acquire ownership over the property she bought until the contract is annulled."
