        "Question": "What is the status of the following marriage and why? A marriage between two Filipino first cousins in Spain where such marriage is valid.",
        "Answer": "VOID. By reason of public policy, the marriage between Filipino first cousins is void (Art. 38(1), FC), and the fact that it is considered a valid marriage in a foreign country in this case, Spain—does not validate it, being an exception to the general rule in Art. 26 of said Code which accords validity to all marriage solemnized outside the Philippines and valid there as such."
