        "Question": "Under what conditions may drug addiction be a ground for an annulment of the marriage contract?",
        "Answer": "Annulment of the marriage contract: 1. The drug addiction must be concealed; 2. It must exist at the time of marriage; 3. There should be no cohabitation with full knowledge of the drug addiction; and 4. The case is filed within 5 years from discovery."
